[See my moderator comments above re: the positive environmental samples. I suspect that these positive environmental samples do reflect continued transmission of the WPV1 among pockets of susceptibles in Pakistan and Afghanistan. I also wonder about how certain one can be that there isn't continued circulation of the WPV1 in inaccessible parts of Nigeria where there are pockets of susceptibles and in other countries that are dealing with civil unrest, leaving pockets of susceptibles (inadequately vaccinated), and with infrastructural disruption seriously impacting upon routine (and emergency) vaccination activities as well as AFP surveillance. As a reminder, the WPV1 responsible for the cluster of polio cases identified in Nigeria in 2016 was most closely related genetically to a virus that had been identified in the area 5 years earlier, suggesting the virus had been "silently" circulating in the area for 5 years. - Mod.MPP]
